    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-05-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-05-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/5–550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-05-05T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 5, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>743. Re <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 27 of January 7. Following is
                    text of <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> dated May 5 in translation from
                    Belgian Foreign Office:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Belgian Government takes note of desire expressed by Government of US to
                        have an exchange of views in next few months with Belgian Government on
                        matter cited in that <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> (of Embassy dated
                            <pb facs="0457" n="441" xml:id="pg_441"/> January 6). It believes, with
                        Government of US, that this consultation would be of interest, and it
                        accepts in principle to participate.</p>
                    <p>“However, since Government of US proposes also to consult French and British
                        Governments on these same subjects, Belgian Government believes that these
                        exchanges of views would be more fruitful if they took place in common.</p>
                    <p>“Belgian Government hopes with government at Washington that these
                        conversations will make it possible to reach an agreement on the means for
                        arriving at a greater comprehension of colonial problems and the respective
                        positions of our government’s confronting them.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Sent Department 743, repeated Paris 152, London 169.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
